2604 /* Khronos platform-specific types and definitions.
2605  *
2606  * The master copy of khrplatform.h is maintained in the Khronos EGL
2607  * Registry repository at https://github.com/KhronosGroup/EGL-Registry
2608  * The last semantic modification to khrplatform.h was at commit ID:
2609  * 67a3e0864c2d75ea5287b9f3d2eb74a745936692
2610  *
2611  * Adopters may modify this file to suit their platform. Adopters are
2612  * encouraged to submit platform specific modifications to the Khronos
2613  * group so that they can be included in future versions of this file.
2614  * Please submit changes by filing pull requests or issues on
2615  * the EGL Registry repository linked above.
2616  *
2617  *
2618  * See the Implementer's Guidelines for information about where this file
2619  * should be located on your system and for more details of its use:
2620  * http://www.khronos.org/registry/implementers_guide.pdf
2621  *
2622  * This file should be included as
2623  * #include <KHR/khrplatform.h>
2624  * by Khronos client API header files that use its types and defines.
2625  *
2626  * The types in khrplatform.h should only be used to define API-specific types.
2627  *
2628  * Types defined in khrplatform.h:
2629  * khronos_int8_t signed 8 bit
2630  * khronos_uint8_t unsigned 8 bit
2631  * khronos_int16_t signed 16 bit
2632  * khronos_uint16_t unsigned 16 bit
2633  * khronos_int32_t signed 32 bit
2634  * khronos_uint32_t unsigned 32 bit
2635  * khronos_int64_t signed 64 bit
2636  * khronos_uint64_t unsigned 64 bit
2637  * khronos_intptr_t signed same number of bits as a pointer
2638  * khronos_uintptr_t unsigned same number of bits as a pointer
2639  * khronos_ssize_t signed size
2640  * khronos_usize_t unsigned size
2641  * khronos_float_t signed 32 bit floating point
2642  * khronos_time_ns_t unsigned 64 bit time in nanoseconds
2643  * khronos_utime_nanoseconds_t unsigned time interval or absolute time in
2644  * nanoseconds
2645  * khronos_stime_nanoseconds_t signed time interval in nanoseconds
2646  * khronos_boolean_enum_t enumerated boolean type. This should
2647  * only be used as a base type when a client API's boolean type is
2648  * an enum. Client APIs which use an integer or other type for
2649  * booleans cannot use this as the base type for their boolean.
2650  *
2651  * Tokens defined in khrplatform.h:
2652  *
2653  * KHRONOS_FALSE, KHRONOS_TRUE Enumerated boolean false/true values.
2654  *
2655  * KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 is 1 if 64 bit integers are supported; otherwise 0.
2656  * KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT is 1 if floats are supported; otherwise 0.
2657  *
2658  * Calling convention macros defined in this file:
2659  * KHRONOS_APICALL
2660  * KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
2661  * KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
2662  *
2663  * These may be used in function prototypes as:
2664  *
2665  * KHRONOS_APICALL void KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR funcname(
2666  * int arg1,
2667  * int arg2) KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES;
2668  */
2669 
2670 #if defined(__SCITECH_SNAP__) && !defined(KHRONOS_STATIC)
2671 # define KHRONOS_STATIC 1
2672 #endif
2673 
2674 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2675  * Definition of KHRONOS_APICALL
2676  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2677  * This precedes the return type of the function in the function prototype.
2678  */
2679 #if defined(KHRONOS_STATIC)
2680  /* If the preprocessor constant KHRONOS_STATIC is defined, make the
2681  * header compatible with static linking. */
2682 # define KHRONOS_APICALL
2683 #elif defined(_WIN32)
2684 # define KHRONOS_APICALL __declspec(dllimport)
2685 #elif defined (__SYMBIAN32__)
2686 # define KHRONOS_APICALL IMPORT_C
2687 #elif defined(__ANDROID__)
2688 # define KHRONOS_APICALL __attribute__((visibility("default")))
2689 #else
2690 # define KHRONOS_APICALL
2691 #endif
2692 
2693 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2694  * Definition of KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
2695  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2696  * This follows the return type of the function and precedes the function
2697  * name in the function prototype.
2698  */
2699 #if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(_WIN32_WCE) && !defined(__SCITECH_SNAP__)
2700  /* Win32 but not WinCE */
2701 # define KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR __stdcall
2702 #else
2703 # define KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
2704 #endif
2705 
2706 /*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2707  * Definition of KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
2708  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2709  * This follows the closing parenthesis of the function prototype arguments.
2710  */
2711 #if defined (__ARMCC_2__)
2712 #define KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES __softfp
2713 #else
2714 #define KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
2715 #endif

2804  */

2810 /*
2811  * Types that differ between LLP64 and LP64 architectures - in LLP64,
2812  * pointers are 64 bits, but 'long' is still 32 bits. Win64 appears
2813  * to be the only LLP64 architecture in current use.
2814  */
2815 #ifdef _WIN64
2816 typedef signed long long int khronos_intptr_t;
2817 typedef unsigned long long int khronos_uintptr_t;
2818 typedef signed long long int khronos_ssize_t;
2819 typedef unsigned long long int khronos_usize_t;
2820 #else
2821 typedef signed long int khronos_intptr_t;
2822 typedef unsigned long int khronos_uintptr_t;
2823 typedef signed long int khronos_ssize_t;
2824 typedef unsigned long int khronos_usize_t;
2825 #endif
2826 
2827 #if KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT
2828 /*
2829  * Float type
2830  */
2831 typedef float khronos_float_t;
2832 #endif
2833 
2834 #if KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64
2835 /* Time types
2836  *
2837  * These types can be used to represent a time interval in nanoseconds or
2838  * an absolute Unadjusted System Time. Unadjusted System Time is the number
2839  * of nanoseconds since some arbitrary system event (e.g. since the last
2840  * time the system booted). The Unadjusted System Time is an unsigned
2841  * 64 bit value that wraps back to 0 every 584 years. Time intervals
2842  * may be either signed or unsigned.
2843  */
2844 typedef khronos_uint64_t khronos_utime_nanoseconds_t;
2845 typedef khronos_int64_t khronos_stime_nanoseconds_t;
2846 #endif
2847 
2848 /*
2849  * Dummy value used to pad enum types to 32 bits.
2850  */
2851 #ifndef KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM
2852 #define KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM 0x7FFFFFFF
2853 #endif
2854 
2855 /*
2856  * Enumerated boolean type
2857  *
2858  * Values other than zero should be considered to be true. Therefore
2859  * comparisons should not be made against KHRONOS_TRUE.
2860  */
2861 typedef enum {
2862  KHRONOS_FALSE = 0,
2863  KHRONOS_TRUE = 1,
2864  KHRONOS_BOOLEAN_ENUM_FORCE_SIZE = KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM
2865 } khronos_boolean_enum_t;

11806 static int sf_glad_gl_get_extensions( int version, const char **out_exts, unsigned int *out_num_exts_i, char ***out_exts_i) {
11807 #if SF_GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION
11808  if(GLAD_VERSION_MAJOR(version) < 3) {
11809 #else
11810  (void) version;
11811  (void) out_num_exts_i;
11812  (void) out_exts_i;
11813 #endif
11814  if (sf_glad_glGetString == NULL) {
11815  return 0;
11816  }
11817  *out_exts = (const char *)sf_glad_glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS);
11818 #if SF_GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION
11819  } else {
11820  unsigned int index = 0;
11821  unsigned int num_exts_i = 0;
11822  char **exts_i = NULL;
11823  if (sf_glad_glGetStringi == NULL || sf_glad_glGetIntegerv == NULL) {
11824  return 0;
11825  }
11826  sf_glad_glGetIntegerv(GL_NUM_EXTENSIONS, (int*) &num_exts_i);
11827  if (num_exts_i > 0) {
11828  exts_i = (char **) malloc(num_exts_i * (sizeof *exts_i));
11829  }
11830  if (exts_i == NULL) {
11831  return 0;
11832  }
11833  for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
11834  const char *gl_str_tmp = (const char*) sf_glad_glGetStringi(GL_EXTENSIONS, index);
11835  size_t len = strlen(gl_str_tmp) + 1;
11836 
11837  char *local_str = (char*) malloc(len * sizeof(char));
11838  if(local_str != NULL) {
11839  memcpy(local_str, gl_str_tmp, len * sizeof(char));
11840  }
11841 
11842  exts_i[index] = local_str;
11843  }
11844 
11845  *out_num_exts_i = num_exts_i;
11846  *out_exts_i = exts_i;
11847  }
11848 #endif
11849  return 1;
11850 }
11851 static void sf_glad_gl_free_extensions(char **exts_i, unsigned int num_exts_i) {
11852  if (exts_i != NULL) {
11853  unsigned int index;
11854  for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
11855  free((void *) (exts_i[index]));
11856  }
11857  free((void *)exts_i);
11858  exts_i = NULL;
11859  }
11860 }
11861 static int sf_glad_gl_has_extension(int version, const char *exts, unsigned int num_exts_i, char **exts_i, const char *ext) {
11862  if(GLAD_VERSION_MAJOR(version) < 3 || !SF_GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION) {
11863  const char *extensions;
11864  const char *loc;
11865  const char *terminator;
11866  extensions = exts;
11867  if(extensions == NULL || ext == NULL) {
11868  return 0;
11869  }
11870  while(1) {
11871  loc = strstr(extensions, ext);
11872  if(loc == NULL) {
11873  return 0;
11874  }
11875  terminator = loc + strlen(ext);
11876  if((loc == extensions || *(loc - 1) == ' ') &&
11877  (*terminator == ' ' || *terminator == '\0')) {
11878  return 1;
11879  }
11880  extensions = terminator;
11881  }
11882  } else {
11883  unsigned int index;
11884  for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
11885  const char *e = exts_i[index];
11886  if(strcmp(e, ext) == 0) {
11887  return 1;
11888  }
11889  }
11890  }
11891  return 0;
11892 }

11894 static GLADapiproc sf_glad_gl_get_proc_from_userptr(void *userptr, const char* name) {
11895  return (GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc (*)(const char *name)) userptr)(name);
11896 }

11995 static int sf_glad_gl_find_core_gl(void) {
11996  int i, major, minor;
11997  const char* version;
11998  const char* prefixes[] = {
11999  "OpenGL ES-CM ",
12000  "OpenGL ES-CL ",
12001  "OpenGL ES ",
12002  NULL
12003  };
12004  version = (const char*) sf_glad_glGetString(GL_VERSION);
12005  if (!version) return 0;
12006  for (i = 0; prefixes[i]; i++) {
12007  const size_t length = strlen(prefixes[i]);
12008  if (strncmp(version, prefixes[i], length) == 0) {
12009  version += length;
12010  break;
12011  }
12012  }
12013 
12014  GLAD_IMPL_UTIL_SSCANF(version, "%d.%d", &major, &minor);
12015 
12016  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_0 = (major == 1 && minor >= 0) || major > 1;
12017  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_1 = (major == 1 && minor >= 1) || major > 1;
12018  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_2 = (major == 1 && minor >= 2) || major > 1;
12019  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_3 = (major == 1 && minor >= 3) || major > 1;
12020  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_4 = (major == 1 && minor >= 4) || major > 1;
12021  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_5 = (major == 1 && minor >= 5) || major > 1;
12022  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_2_0 = (major == 2 && minor >= 0) || major > 2;
12023  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_2_1 = (major == 2 && minor >= 1) || major > 2;
12024  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_0 = (major == 3 && minor >= 0) || major > 3;
12025  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_1 = (major == 3 && minor >= 1) || major > 3;
12026  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_2 = (major == 3 && minor >= 2) || major > 3;
12027  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_3 = (major == 3 && minor >= 3) || major > 3;
12028  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_0 = (major == 4 && minor >= 0) || major > 4;
12029  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_1 = (major == 4 && minor >= 1) || major > 4;
12030  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_2 = (major == 4 && minor >= 2) || major > 4;
12031  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_3 = (major == 4 && minor >= 3) || major > 4;
12032  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_4 = (major == 4 && minor >= 4) || major > 4;
12033  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_5 = (major == 4 && minor >= 5) || major > 4;
12034  SF_GLAD_GL_VERSION_4_6 = (major == 4 && minor >= 6) || major > 4;
12035 
12036  return GLAD_MAKE_VERSION(major, minor);
12037 }
